{"questionId":"13925671","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The computer then selects at random an integer <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>, inclusive. Each outcome is equally likely.</p>\n<p>Daniel is trying to determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> and asks if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>. He is told that it is not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the probability that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> is odd.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13925671","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2bi","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the probability that x is odd.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
